    "description": "We at Abbott India Holdings Services are looking for an experienced Radiologist based out of Pimpri-Chinchwad. If you are a result-oriented professional with a passion for excellence, we want to hear from you.\n\nAbout Abbott India Holdings Services:\nAbbott India Holdings Services is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Administer medications and treatments as prescribed\n• Coordinate with multidisciplinary teams for comprehensive patient management\n• Attend continuing medical education programs and training\n• Educate patients and families on health management and disease prevention\n• Participate in quality improvement initiatives and clinical audits\n• Maintain sterile environments and follow infection control protocols\n• Adhere to NABH/JCI accreditation standards\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Sc / M.Sc in Life Sciences\n• 12-20 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Patient Care\n• Proficiency in Clinical Documentation\n• Proficiency in Infection Control\n• Proficiency in EMR/EHR\n• Proficiency in Medical Coding\n• Proficiency in BLS/ACLS\n• Proficiency in Diagnostic Skills\n• Proficiency in Pharmacovigilance\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Learning & development budget\n• Salary Range: 35 LPA - 70 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Pimpri-Chinchwad, Maharashtra, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Abbott India Holdings Services!",
